als]]\n[[Category:20th-century apocalypticists]]\n[[Category:Activists for African-American civil rights]]\n[[Category:Activists who committed suicide]]\n[[Category:American anti-war activists]]\n[[Category:American anti\u2013Vietnam War activists]]\n[[Category:American clergy of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American former Christians]]\n[[Category:American agnostics]]\n[[Category:American atheists]]\n[[Category:American communists]]\n[[Category:American conspiracy theorists]]\n[[Category:American emigrants to Brazil]]\n[[Category:American emigrants to Guyana]]\n[[Category:American male criminals]]\n[[Category:American mass murderers]]\n[[Category:American murderers of children]]\n[[Category:American socialists]]\n[[Category:Murderers who committed suicide]]\n[[Category:American people of Welsh descent]]\n[[Category:Bisexual men]]\n[[Category:Butler University alumni]]\n[[Category:Christian Church (Disciples of Christ) clergy]]\n[[Category:Converts from Methodism]]\n[[Category:Criminals from Indiana]]\n[[Category:Criminals who committed suicide]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Guyana]]\n[[Category:American faith healers]]\n[[Category:Founders of new religious movements]]\n[[Category:Founders of utopian communities]]\n[[Category:History of Guyana]]\n[[Category:LGBT Calvinist and Reformed Christians]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Indiana]]\n[[Category:LGBT Protestant clergy]]\n[[Category:Male suicides]]\n[[Category:People from Randolph County, Indiana]]\n[[Category:People from Richmond, Indiana]]\n[[Category:Peoples Temple]]\n[[Category:Crime in Guyana]]\n[[Category:Religious leaders from the San Francisco Bay Area]]\n[[Category:Self-declared messiahs]]\n[[Category:Suicides by firearm]]\n[[Category:Suicides in Guyana]]\n", "name_user": "24.228.117.14", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jim_Jones"}
{"title_page": "Subnautica Below Zero", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 video game}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{copy edit|date=April 2020}}{{Sources exist|date=April 2020}}{{Confusing|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Subnautica Below Zero\n| image = \n| caption = \n| developer = [[Unknown Worlds Entertainment]]\n| publisher = Unknown Worlds Entertainment\n| director = Charlie Cleveland\n| producer = \n| designer = \n| programmer = \n| artist = {{Unbulleted list|Cory Strader|Brian Cummings|Scott MacDonald\n<ref name=\"Crew\">{{cite web|last=Jeremy|first=Hugh|title=The Crew of Subnautica|url=http://unknownworlds.com/subnautica/the-crew-of-subnautica/|publisher=[[Unknown Worlds Entertainment]]|date=December 17, 2013|access-date=April 9, 2016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417144732/http://unknownworlds.com/subnautica/the-crew-of-subnautica/|archive-date=April 17, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref>}}\n| writer = [[Tom Jubert]]\n| composer =\n| engine = [[Unity (game engine)|Unity]]\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[MacOS]]}}\n| released = \n| genre = {{hlist|[[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]]|[[survival game|survival]]}}\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]]\n}}\n\n'''''Subnautica Below Zero''''' is an [[open world|open-world]] [[Survival game|survival]] [[Action-adventure game|action-adventure]] video game developed and published by [[Unknown Worlds Entertainment]]. It is the sequel to ''[[Subnautica]]'', which was released in January 2018.\n\n''Subnautica Below Zero'' was released in [[early access]] for Microsoft Windows and macOS in January 2019. \n\n== Gameplay ==\n''Subnautica Below Zero'' is a [[Survival game|survival]], [[Adventure game|adventure]] game set in an [[open world]] environment and played from a [[First-person (video games)|first-person perspective]]. The player controls a researcher researching the local environment and nearby alien facility, on planet 4546B.\n\n== Plot ==\n''Subnautica Below Zero'' takes place two years after the ending of ''[[Subnautica]]''. Alterra has placed the Vesper Station into orbit around the planet 4546B for research. The story opens with the Player being told to head to the nearby Mountain Alien Facility to locate Serik Jevov (Jeff). The player then encounters the voice of one of the architects, letting the player know that Jeff is gone; the Alien Facility then gets locked off and requires a White Tablet to enter. Afterward, the Alien Facility is  struck by a meteor and begins re-routing its power to Sanctuary. The player is told to get to the escape ship back at base. However, the ship takes off, and the player has to take shelter in Research Base Zero. After the meteor shower triggers an Avalanche, the ice breaks below the player causing them to have to swim out into open water, and head to a Lifepod launched by Sam Goodall on the Vesper Station, just before The Vesper is struck by a meteorite damaging its communication ability. \n\nShortly after, the player receives a message tracked to the Alien Sanctuary Site in the Twist Bridges. Once the player is exploring the Underwater Alien Facility, they are threatened by an Alien voice saying that its storage medium is failing. As the player reaches the inner of the Alien Facility, it notes that is has found an \"adequate storage medium\". The player offers their PDA for the consciousnesses to transfer into. However, it transfers into the player's Cerebral Cortex. The Alien Voice then lets the player knows its name is Al-an.\n\nAs the player approaches Rocket Island, their PDA informs them that repairing the communications tower will reestablish contact with The Vesper, requiring the player to explore the Mercury II wreck, a ship that crashed anywhere from 30 to 100 years ago. After The Player repairs the communications tower, they are told that the ship - took off at the beginning of the game, crash-landed in the Glacial Basin and that they have three objectives: Find Jeff, extract a sample of the Kharaa sample and retrieve research data from Research Base Omega.\n\nIn the Glacial Basin, the player finds the crashed escape ship. The player can locate Jeff's base in the Glacial Basin and is informed that Jeff is most likely in another sector. The player is then told to head to the Leviathan Genetic Research Program to receive a sample of the Kharaa Bacterium and send it up to The Vesper. As the player explores the Glacial Basin, they find a Cache with one of the architect's body parts.  A while after the player sends the Kharaa Bacterium, they get a message saying that it never arrived. The player then gets a supply drop in the Lilypad Islands leading them towards Research Base Omega. Throughout the player's adventure, they find two more caches, each containing one of the other parts to the architect's body. When the player arrives in the Fabricator Base, they are told that they are able to construct Al-an a body and transfer his consciousness back into it.\n\nThe player gets contacted by Sam to be told that the Vesper's supply of Enzyme 42 deteriorated overnight and that they need a sample from a nearby Sea Emperor Leviathan. As the player sends the Enzyme up to The Vesper, an architect shield covers the planet causing the rocket containing the cure to explode. The player then calls Robin and the mission director about what happened. Jeff then joins the call and says his intention to hold the Vesper crew hostage as they are most likely exposed to the Kharaa bacterium, alongside the player being trapped on the surface. The Player then learns from Al-an that they need to head to the Mountain Alien Facility \n\nAfter the player receives the white tablet to enter the facility, they head to the Alien Facility and enter it.  The game ends with The Vesper station being blown up.\n\n<!--== Plot == how are there two different plots? That needs explaining for inclusion.\n\n''Subnautica Below Zero'' takes place two years after the ending of Subnautica. Alterra is funding a smaller company called XenoWorks, which the player works for. The player heads down on a shuttle to the surface of 4546B trying to \"cover from Alterra satellites\" to find their sister, Sam. On the way down, a meteor crashes into the player causing their lifepod to deploy and them to crash land in Sector Zero.\n-->\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [https://unknownworlds.com/subnautica/ Official website]\n\n{{uncategorised|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 video game}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{copy edit|date=April 2020}}{{Sources exist|date=April 2020}}{{Confusing|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Subnautica Below Zero\n| image = \n| caption = \n| developer = [[Unknown Worlds Entertainment]]\n| publisher = Unknown Worlds Entertainment\n| director = Charlie Cleveland\n| producer = \n| designer = \n| programmer = \n| artist = {{Unbulleted list|Cory Strader|Brian Cummings|Scott MacDonald\n<ref name=\"Crew\">{{cite web|last=Jeremy|first=Hugh|title=The Crew of Subnautica|url=http://unknownworlds.com/subnautica/the-crew-of-subnautica/|publisher=[[Unknown Worlds Entertainment]]|date=December 17, 2013|access-date=April 9, 2016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417144732/http://unknownworlds.com/subnautica/the-crew-of-subnautica/|archive-date=April 17, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref>}}\n| writer = [[Tom Jubert]]\n| composer =\n| engine = [[Unity (game engine)|Unity]]\n| platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[Microsoft Windows]]|[[MacOS]]}}\n| released = \n| genre = {{hlist|[[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]]|[[survival game|survival]]}}\n| modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]]\n}}\n\n'''''Subnautica Below Zero''''' is an [[open world]] [[Survival game|survival]] [[Action-adventure game|action-adventure]] video game developed and published by [[Unknown Worlds Entertainment]]. It is the sequel to ''[[Subnautica]]'', which was released in January 2018.\n\n''Subnautica Below Zero'' was released in [[early access]] for Microsoft Windows and macOS in January 2019. \n\n== Gameplay ==\n''Subnautica Below Zero'' is a [[Survival game|survival]], [[Adventure game|adventure]] game set in an [[open world]] environment and played from a [[First-person (video games)|first-person perspective]]. The player controls a researcher researching the local environment and nearby alien facility, on planet 4546B.\n\n== Plot ==\n''Subnautica Below Zero'' takes place two years after the ending of ''[[Subnautica]]''. Alterra has placed the Vesper Station into orbit around the planet 4546B for research. The story opens with the Player being told to head to the nearby Mountain Alien Facility to locate Serik Jevov (Jeff). The player then encounters the voice of one of The Architects, letting the player know that Jeff is gone; the Alien Facility then gets locked off and requires a White Tablet to enter. Afterward, the Alien Facility is  struck by a meteor and begins re-routing its power to Sanctuary. The player is told to get to the escape ship back at base, however, the ship takes off, and the player has to take shelter in Research Base Zero. After the meteor shower triggers an Avalanche, the ice breaks below the player causing them to have to swim out into open water, and head to a Lifepod launched by Sam Goodall on the Vesper Station, just before The Vesper is struck by a meteorite damaging its communication ability. \n\nShortly after, the player receives a message tracked to the Alien Sanctuary Site in the Twist Bridges. Once the player is exploring the Underwater Alien Facility, they are threatened by an Alien voice saying that its storage medium is failing. As the player reaches the inner of the Alien Facility, it notes that is has found an \"adequate storage medium\". The player offers their PDA for the consciousnesses to transfer into, however, it transfers into the players Cerebral Cortex. The Alien Voice then lets the player knows its name is Al-an.\n\nAs the player approaches Rocket Island, their PDA informs them that repairing the communications tower will reestablish contact with The Vesper, requiring the player to explore the Mercury II wreck, a ship that crashed anywhere from 30 to 100 years ago. After The Player repairs the communications tower, they are told the ship that took off at the beginning of the game crash-landed in the Glacial Basin and that they have three objectives: Find Jeff, extract a sample of the Kharaa sample and retrieve research data from Research Base Omega.\n\nIn the Glacial Basin, the player finds the crashed escape ship. The player can locate Jeff's base in the Glacial Basin and is informed that Jeff is most likely in another sector. The player is then told to head to the Leviathan Genetic Research Program to receive a sample of the Kharaa Bacterium and send it up to The Vesper. As the player explores the Glacial Basin, they find a Cache with one of The Architect body parts.  A while after the player sends the Kharaa Bacterium, they get a message saying that it never arrived. The player then gets a supply drop in the Lilypad Islands leading them towards Research Base Omega. Throughout the player's adventure, they find two more caches, each containing one of the other parts to The Architect's body. When the player arrives in the Fabricator Base, they are told that they are able to construct Al-an a body and transfer his consciousness back into it.\n\nThe Player gets contacted by Sam to be told that The Vesper's supply of Enzyme 42 deteriorated overnight and that they need a sample from a nearby Sea Emperor Leviathan. As the player sends the Enzyme up to The Vesper, an Architect shield covers the planet causing the rocket containing the cure to explode. The player then calls Robin and the Mission director about what happened, Jeff then joins the call and says his intention to hold the Vesper crew hostage as they are most likely exposed to the Kharaa bacterium, alongside The Player being trapped on the surface. The Player then learns from Al-an that they need to head to the Mountain Alien Facility \n\nAfter the player receives the White tablet to enter the facility, they head to the Alien Facility and enter it.  The game ends with The Vesper station being blown up.\n\n<!--== Plot == how are there two different plots? That needs explaining for inclusion.\n\n''Subnautica Below Zero'' takes place two years after the ending of Subnautica. Alterra is funding a smaller company called XenoWorks, which the player works for. The player heads down on a shuttle to the surface of 4546B trying to \"cover from Alterra satellites\" to find their sister, Sam. On the way down, a meteor crashes into the player causing their lifepod to deploy and them to crash land in Sector Zero.\n-->\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* [https://unknownworlds.com/subnautica/ Official website]\n\n{{uncategorised|date=April 2020}}\n", "name_user": "Staahnz", "label": "safe", "comment": "Changed many grammatical mistakes in the article", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subnautica_Below_Zero"}
{"title_page": "Prudhvi Raj", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Pruthviraj\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Balireddy Pruthviraj\n| birth_place        = [[Tadepalligudem]], [[West Godavari district]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| residence          = [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]], [[India]],\n[[Tirupati|Tirupathi]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| father             = Balireddy Subbarao\n| occupation         = Actor, Politician, Ex-SVBC channel chairman\n| education          = M.A\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1964|8|6}}\n| alma_mater         = [[Andhra University]], [[Visakhapatnam]]\n| Political party    = [[YSR Congress Party]]\n}}\n\n'''Balireddy Prudhviraj''' (born August 6, 1964) is a comedian in [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]].<ref name=\"Times of India News1\">{{cite web|last1=Hemanth|first1=Kumar|title=Prudhvi Raj gets rave reviews for his role in Loukyam|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Prudhvi-Raj-gets-rave-reviews-for-his-role-in-Loukyam/articleshow/43525908.cms|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|publisher=Times of India|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"deccanchronicle\">{{cite web|last1=Kavirayani|first1=Suresh|title=It\u2019s not been an easy journey: Prudhviraj|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150805/entertainment-tollywood/article/it%E2%80%99s-not-been-easy-journey-prudhviraj|website=deccanchronicle.com|publisher=Deccan Chronicle|accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref> He was introduced by [[Prabhakar Reddy]].<ref name=\"Telugu 360 interview\">{{cite web|last1=Yalavarthi|first1=Sunita|title=Exclusive Interview with Prudhviraj (30 years industry)|url=https://www.telugu360.com/exclusive-interview-with-prudhviraj-comedian/|website=telugu360.com|publisher=Telugu 360|accessdate=12 December 2016}}</ref> Later he acted in ''[[Aa Okkati Adakku]]''. During this movie Prudhviraj spent 40 days with [[Rao Gopala Rao]] where he learned about the industry. He acted in more than 100 movies. He is noted for his role of \"30 Years Industry\", in [[Krishna Vamsi|Krishna Vamsi's]] movie, ''[[Khadgam]]''.<ref name=\"thehindu.com\">{{cite web|last1=Y.|first1=Sunita Chowdhary|title=Patience pays, finally for Prudhviraj|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/the-actor-is-in-demand-for-a-lot-of-comic-roles/article8029001.ece|website=thehindu.com|publisher=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teluguportals.com/2012/03/tori-live-show-with-4/#.UEOnlGYpLzo |title=TORI Live Show with Comedian Prithviraj |publisher=teluguportals.com |date=2012-03-14 |accessdate=2012-10-01}}</ref> He worked as chairman of [[SVBC TV|SVBC]] channel which was run by [[Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanams]] until January 12, 2020.\n\nOn January 11, 2020, an obscene illicit conversation between Prudhviraj and his female employee working in SVBC was found out and broadcast by the channel [[99TV]]. Subsequently he was found guilty and was asked to resign from his SVBC chairman post.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m6VdbkNRjOo</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nPrudhviraj (born Balireddy Prudhviraj), is a famous comedian in [[Telugu film industry]]. He was born August 6 at [[Tadepalligudem]], West Godavari District, Andhra Pradesh. He was introduced by famous Dr. Prabakar Reddy and [[E V V Satyanarayana]] in their first film ''[[Aa Okkati Adakku]]''. During this film he spent forty days with [[Rao Gopala Rao]], where he learnt about the film industry. He played many roles in about 100 films. He was well recognized for his dialogue \u201c30 Years Industry ikkada\u201d in [[Krishna Vamsi]]'s film ''[[Khadgam]]'' and this film changed his fate.\n\nPrudhviraj hails from a respected farmer family in Tadepalligudem. Prudhviraj completed his master's degree in Economics from Andhra University. Since childhood, he participated in many stage shows and cultural activities. From his childhood, he had a dream to work in movies. With that interest, he entered into the industry. Prudhvi Raj's mother also supported him a lot to enter into the industry. After his debut film \u201cAa Okkati Adakku\u201d he left Chennai. Then Prudhviraj tried his luck in [[Tamil film industry]] but unfortunately he failed there.\n\nAgain he returned to the Telugu film industry and tested his luck. With the movie Kadgam, Prudhviraj became very popular. Before acting in Kadgam he worked in a hotel as a receptionist and also in a guest house.\n\nPrudhviraj is mostly suitable for comedy roles. His dialogue delivery and comedy in films is very effective. He had a well-noted role in the movie Loukyam.\n\nPrudhviraj played roles with top Tollywood actors such as [[Ravi Teja]], [[Daggubati Venkatesh|Venkatesh]], [[Ram Charan]], [[Pawan Kalyan]], [[Mahesh Babu]], [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad's]], [[Allu Arjun]], [[Gopichand (actor)|Gopichand]] and [[Nithiin]].\n\nHe has been nominated as chairman of [[SVBC TV|Sri Venkateswara Bhakti Channel]] in 2019. On 11 January 2020, his Audio tape recording with female employee of SVBC channel went viral in Youtube and SVBC employees protested urging him to resign from his post of chairman of Svbc channel.\n\nOn 11 January 2020, Prudhviraj resigned as chairman of [[SVBC TV|Sri Venkateswara Bhakti Channel]].\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Film{{efn|name=fn1|Films are listed in the order of their release date}}\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''[[Khaidi No. 420]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''[[Ladies Tailor (1985 film)|Ladies Tailor]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Gandipeta Rahasyam]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[Intinta Deepavali]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[Prema Khaidi]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Nagastram]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[Aa Okkati Adakku]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Ninne Pelladata]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''[[Sindhooram]]''\n| Naxalite\n|\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[Ganesh (film)|Ganesh]]''\n| Dr. Anand\n|\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[Chandralekha (1998 film)|Chandralekha]]''\n| Ramaraju\n|\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Samudram (1999 film)|Samudram]]''\n| Police Officer\n|\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Bachi (film)|Bachi]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Devullu]]''\n| [[Lord Venkateshwara]]\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Idiot (2002 film)|Idiot]]''\n| Police Officer\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Khadgam]]''\n| 30 Years Industry\n|\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Ammayi (Telugu film)|Ammayi]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Arya (2004 film)|Arya]]''\n| Reddy\n|\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Sri Anjaneyam]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Okkade]]''\n| Police Officer\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Ranam (2006 film)|Ranam]]''\n| Police Inspector\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Pokiri]]''\n| Vishwanath\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Pudhupettai]]''\n| Murthy\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Dhee]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Ready (2008 film)|Ready]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Souryam]]''\n| Police Officer\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Yuvatha]]''\n| Krishna Manohar\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2009\n| ''[[Sasirekha Parinayam]]''\n| Lorry Driver\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Fitting Master]]''\n| Police Officer\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Kick (2009 film)|Kick]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Current (2009 film)|Current]]''\n| Police Officer\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Snehituda...]]''\n| Police Officer\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Sankham]]''\n| Pasupati's brother-in-law\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Ek Niranjan]]''\n| Ex-Minister\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2010\n| ''[[Adhurs]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Namo Venkatesa]]''\n| Prasad's Gang Member\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Rama Rama Krishna Krishna]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Prasthanam]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Vedam (film)|Vedam]]''\n| Bullebbayi\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2011\n| ''[[Aha Naa Pellanta (2011 film)|Aha Naa Pellanta]]''\n| Pilot\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Dookudu]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2012\n| ''